{"type":"message","id":"be0c34d7","parentId":"3515f7ef","timestamp":"2026-02-15T11:28:58.779Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[Sun 2026-02-15 13:28 GMT+2] FEATURE EXTRACTION & UPGRADE (Pro Stream).\n\n1.  **Claude Code Analysis:**\n    *   Research `Claude Code CLI` features.\n    *   *Key Findings:*\n        *   **Compact Context:** Auto-summarization of old messages to keep context window clean.\n        *   **Slash Commands:** `/fix`, `/test`, `/diff` for immediate actions without NL parsing overhead.\n        *   **Lazy Reading:** `grep` / `read_snippet` instead of `read_file` for massive codebases.\n\n2.  **Google Engineering (Antigravity/IDX):**\n    *   Check `antigravity.google` (likely internal/easter egg). Fallback to **Project IDX**.\n    *   *Key Principles:* **Zero-Config Environments** (Nix-based), **Instant Previews** (Live feedback), **AI-Assisted Refactoring**.\n\n3.  **Feature Extraction (Top 3):**\n    1.  **Slash Commands (`/fix`, `/search`):** Implement a lightweight router in `agent_wrapper.py` or system prompt.\n    2.  **Lazy Context (`/compact`):** Implement a tool/skill that summarizes the current session history into `memory/current_context.md` and clears the chat log.\n    3.  **Instant Feedback (`/test`):** A command that immediately runs `pytest` on the last edited file.\n\n4.  **Implementation (The \"Superpower\"):**\n    *   **Chosen Feature:** **Slash Commands (`/fix`, `/test`, `/compact`)**.\n    *   *Action:* Update `CORE_PROTOCOLS_2026.md` to define these commands.\n    *   *Demo:* Execute a simulated `/test` command that triggers `pytest` on `dmarket_api.py`.\n\n5.  **Output:**\n    *   Competitor Analysis Report.\n    *   List of Adopted Features.\n    *   Live Demo of `/test` command."}],"timestamp":1771154938777}}
