{"type":"message","id":"9a548b57","parentId":"577775f6","timestamp":"2026-02-15T11:30:15.373Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Considering the Setup**\n\nI've confirmed `nacl` is installed without issues. The next step is to get the test file `tests/test_dmarket_api_demo.py` built and in place, within the `DMarket-Telegram-Bot-main` directory. I'm focusing on the `sys.path` modifications to ensure the import of `dmarket_api` is possible.\n\n\n**Defining the Tests**\n\nI'm now outlining the test structure. The `test_dmarket_api_demo.py` file will include tests for `get_balance` and `get_market_prices`. I'll use `requests.get` mocking to provide a controlled environment. Specifically, the tests will validate URL construction and header integrity.\n\n\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"write_1771155015345_405","name":"write","arguments":{"content":"import unittest\nfrom unittest.mock import MagicMock, patch\nimport sys\nimport os\n\n# Add parent directory to path to import dmarket_api\nsys.path.append(os.path.dirname(os.path.dirname(os.path.abspath(__file__))))\n\nfrom dmarket_api import DMarketClient\n\nclass TestDMarketClientDemo(unittest.TestCase):\n    def setUp(self):\n        # Mock environment variables or config\n        self.public_key = \"test_pub\"\n        self.private_key = \"746573745f70726976\" # hex for \"test_priv\"\n        \n        self.client = DMarketClient(public_key=self.public_key, private_key=self.private_key)\n\n    @patch('dmarket_api.requests.get')\n    def test_get_balance_success(self, mock_get):\n        # Setup mock response\n        mock_response = MagicMock()\n        mock_response.json.return_value = {\"usd\": 100.0, \"dmc\": 50.0}\n        mock_response.raise_for_status.return_value = None\n        mock_get.return_value = mock_response\n\n        # Execute\n        balance = self.client.get_balance()\n\n        # Assert\n        self.assertEqual(balance[\"usd\"], 100.0)\n        self.assertEqual(balance[\"dmc\"], 50.0)\n        \n        # Verify URL and Headers\n        expected_url = \"https://api.dmarket.com/account/v1/balance\"\n        mock_get.assert_called_once()\n        args, kwargs = mock_get.call_args\n        self.assertEqual(args[0], expected_url)\n        self.assertIn(\"X-Api-Key\", kwargs['headers'])\n        self.assertEqual(kwargs['headers'][\"X-Api-Key\"], self.public_key)\n\n    @patch('dmarket_api.requests.get')\n    def test_get_market_prices_success(self, mock_get):\n        # Setup mock response\n        mock_response = MagicMock()\n        mock_response.json.return_value = {\"items\": []}\n        mock_get.return_value = mock_response\n\n        # Execute\n        self.client.get_market_prices(game_id=\"csgo\")\n\n        # Verify URL\n        expected_url = \"https://api.dmarket.com/price-aggregator/v1/aggregated-prices?GameID=csgo\"\n        mock_get.assert_called_once()\n        self.assertTrue(mock_get.call_args[0][0].endswith(\"GameID=csgo\"))\n\nif __name__ == '__main__':\n    unittest.main()\n","file_path":"DMarket-Telegram-Bot-main/tests/test_dmarket_api_demo.py"},"thoughtSignature":""}],"api":"google-vertex","provider":"google-vertex","model":"gemini-3-pro-preview","usage":{"input":13807,"output":806,"cacheRead":12568,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":14613,"cost":{"input":0.027614,"output":0.009672,"cacheRead":0.0025136000000000004,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0397996}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1771154996609}}
